  "text": "It has been revealed that vehicle fuel consumption functions are too complex to be approximated in practice due to numerous variables affecting their outcome [CITATION_1] . In particular, most of the proposed mathematical models consider a set of parameters from different categories such as vehicle engine, traffic, road, vehicle, weather and driver related categories (Van den Brink, [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Thus, for example, for a given vehicle and engine type fuel consumption in a random trip depends to varying degrees on a number of parameters such as speed and acceleration patterns, gear changing management, road grade and surface, traffic density and velocity, number of vehicle stops, weather conditions such as temperature, wind speed, etc.",
